When at last she left, I lost another hourcomposing a detailed letter asking her never to come back. Incidentally, itwas the first time that an unfinished leaf was left by her in my typewriter.I removed it and rediscovered it several weeks later among my papers, andthen deliberately preserved it because it was Annette who completed the job,with a couple of typos and an x-ed erasure in the last lines--and somethingabout the juxtaposition appealed to my combinational slant. <84>3

